      "current_heading": "Content",
      "comment_text": "I will have to think about sequencing the endgame fights. Right now it’s kind of Davian-heavy and Maya is not doing as much. If Davian comes into the throne room with Serathis and Niall, then he has to go free his mom and come back and Maya is still fighting Serathis, and then she leaves, Davian and Kelyra kill Serathis, and then he goes down and helps Maya and Niall. So what are some options? Davian goes off on his own to find his mom, somehow - maybe they get info from a spy or Aldira’s sources where she is specifically - and he splits off when they enter the Archeon citadel. However after Serathis triggers the trap for Niall it just leaves Maya fighting Serathis alone until Davian and Kelyra come. That’s an issue for a couple reasons, one of is that Maya should be able to beat Serathis. Serathis could summon a TON of her kids which is somewhat plausible but then why wouldn’t she have sent them to get Davian? Could be she didn’t realize how valuable Davian was until Kelyra came back? So she kept back a ton, and Maya kills a bunch of them until Davian comes back - which is why it’s just him fighting Serathis (with Kelyra) instead of the other Archeon people? But then those people are all dead which could be a future issue.",
      "status": "inbox"
    },
